            <a:r>
              <a:rPr lang="en-US" dirty="0"/>
              <a:t>Without handoff artifacts, workers communicate only through text — the next worker has to parse prose. With them, a data_analyst produces an analysis_summary artifact with structured highlights and keywords, and a subsequent rag_worker consumes it via list_handoff_artifacts(session, allowed_consumers=['rag_worker']). Allowed_consumers enforces access control: doc_focus is visible to data analysts but entity_candidates isn't. register_handoff_artifact() stores the artifact in session.metadata as a list of dicts. Each gets a unique artifact_id, type, producer task_id, summary string, and data payload. KernelCoordinatorController._prepare_handoff_artifacts() is called after each TaskResult. It calls _handoff_payload() to extract fields: for analysis_summary it takes the first 4000 chars plus highlights; for entity_candidates it regex-scans for capitalized multi-word tokens; for doc_focus it uses the task's doc_scope. It validates each payload against _HANDOFF_SCHEMA_KEYS — invalid ones are logged and skipped.</a:t>
            </a:r>
          </a:p>
        </p:txBody>
